Content:: Alexis Gougeard (born 5 March 1993 in Rouen) is a French cyclist, who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam AG2R Citroën Team.[4] He specializes in time trials and track cycling. He became professional in 2014, as a member of the Ag2r–La Mondiale team. He was named in the start list for the 2015 Vuelta a España,[5] where he took his first grand tour stage win on the nineteenth stage, making a winning attack from a breakaway group.[6]  This biographical article related to a French cycling person born in the 1990s is a stub.
